==English==
=== Noun ===
'''surmise'''
#  thought, imagination, or conjecture, which may be based upon feeble or scanty evidence; suspicion; guess; as, surmises of jealousy or of envy.
 
#  Reflection; thought.  Posit.

'''surmisal'''
#  n.,   a surmising, the act of surmising.

=== Verb ===
# To conjecture, to opine or to posit with contestable premise(s).  Internet usage in correspondence and blogging: roughly equivalent to IMHO, (I Might Hazard Opinion), or IMO, (In My Opinion).